Operatives of the Eagle-Net Special Squad have arrested a twenty-year-old passenger, Edea Samuel ‘m’ age 20yrs with a large quàntity of illicit and hard drugs. The suspect was apprehended along the Asaba Ogwashi-Uku expressway in Delta State. The arrest came after the Police intercepted a commercial vehicle which they subjected to a search. In the process, the Police recovered four thousand and fifty-four {4054} wraps of substance suspected to be cocaine, nine hundred and fifty-four {954} wraps of heroines on a bag belonging to one of the passengers who is resident at Ochele Street off Ojugbana Drive Ezenei, Asaba. The Delta State Police Command led by CP Ari Muhammed Ali confirmed the report in a statement signed by the Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe. He said,” Investigation is ongoing.”